<h1>@HI{{teineigo}}: Polite Language</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{teineigo}} are polite expressions to show the speaker's respect for the listener.
</p>


<h3> @HI{{gozaimasu}} </h3>

<p>
@HI{{gozaimasu}} is the polite equivalent of @HI{{arimasu}}.
</p>

<h3> @HI{{gozaimasu}} </h3>

<p>
@HI{{de gozaimasu}} is the polite equivalent of @HI{{desu}}.
</p>

<h3> @HI{{yoroshiideshouka}} </h3>

<p>
@HI{{yoroshiideshouka}} is the polite equivalent of @HI{{ii desu ka}}.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{electricity^tale}}ha @KJ{{storey^grade}}no @KJ{{sideways}} gozaimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The pay phone is beside the stairs.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{hai,}} IMC@HI{{de gozaimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Hello, this is IMC.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{ko-hi-}}wo o@KJ{{petition}}ishimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Coffee please.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KT{{panfuretto}}wo itadaitemo yoroshiideshouka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      May I have one of these pamphlets?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

